//PrintWriter is a high-level writer used to write formatted text data to files.
//It provides convenient methods like print(), println(), and printf()
//which are similar to System.out.println(), making it very easy to use.
//
//While FileWriter and BufferedWriter can write characters,
//PrintWriter adds user-friendly printing features and automatic flushing support.
//
//PrintWriter does NOT throw IOException for write operations;
//instead, errors can be checked using checkError() method.
//
//We typically wrap PrintWriter on top of FileWriter or BufferedWriter
//to get:
//- FileWriter / BufferedWriter → low-level file writing
//- PrintWriter → easy printing with print(), println(), printf()
//if we use  print(), println(), printf(), the value what we entered will get stored in file
